---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import ConsultationFlow from '../../components/ConsultationFlow.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="Corporate Mental Health Helpdesk | Wa-Node" description="External mental health helpdesk for small businesses & SMEs with 50 or fewer employees. Supporting a healthy work environment." noindex={true}>
  <main>
    <section class="hero">
      <div class="wrap">
        <p class="kicker">Corporate Mental Health</p>
        <h1>So your employees' worries<br />don't remain bottled up inside.</h1>
        <p class="lead">
          Wa-Node's corporate mental health consultation is an external helpdesk tailored for small businesses and SMEs with 50 or fewer employees. We support early identification of mental strain and create an accessible workplace through anonymous individual consulting, monthly reports, and HR coordinator consultations.
          <strong>*When handling consultation content from employees, we explain and obtain consent regarding confidentiality, the scope of corporate sharing, emergency exceptions, and data retention periods before starting.</strong>
        </p>
        <div class="btns">
          <a class="btn primary" href="https://lin.ee/o5QFPwc" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Consult via LINE</a>
          <a class="btn secondary" href="#consultation-flow">Check Consultation Steps</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section>
      <div class="wrap grid three">
        <div class="card">
          <span class="badge">Target</span>
          <h3>50 or Fewer Employees</h3>
          <p>Ideal for small businesses and SMEs that struggle to maintain a dedicated HR or mental health department.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <span class="badge">Contract</span>
          <h3>Minimum 3 Months</h3>
          <p>Rather than one-time short-term intervention, we provide ongoing support while analyzing workplace stress trends.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <span class="badge">Reports</span>
          <h3>Anonymized Reports</h3>
          <p>We avoid sharing personally identifiable details, focusing strictly on case volume, stress categories, and improvement suggestions.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="mental-stats-section" style="background: var(--paper); border-top: 1px solid var(--line); border-bottom: 1px solid var(--line); padding: 60px 0;">
      <div class="wrap">
        <div class="section-head" style="text-align: center; margin-bottom: 40px;">
          <p class="kicker">Data & Evidence</p>
          <h2>Mental Health Issues & the ROI of Support Programs</h2>
          <p class="muted">Employee mental strain is not just a personal struggle; it is a critical issue directly affecting organizational sustainability.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="grid two" style="gap: 32px; max-width: 900px; margin: 0 auto;">
          <div class="card stat-card" style="display: flex; flex-direction: column; align-items: center; text-align: center; padding: 36px 24px;">
            <span class="badge" style="background: rgba(209, 77, 58, 0.1); color: var(--accent2);">Current Challenges</span>
            <div class="stat-number" style="font-size: clamp(3rem, 6vw, 4.5rem); font-weight: 900; color: var(--accent2); line-height: 1.1; margin: 16px 0;">82.7<span style="font-size: 1.8rem; font-weight: 800;">%</span></div>
            <h4 style="font-size: 1.15rem; font-weight: 800; margin-bottom: 12px; color: var(--text-deep);">Ratio of Employees Facing High Stress</h4>
            <p style="font-size: 0.92rem; color: var(--muted); line-height: 1.6; margin: 0;">
              This represents the percentage of workers experiencing intense anxiety or stress in their jobs, based on the Ministry of Health, Labour and Welfare's 2023 Occupational Health and Safety Survey. Regardless of company size, many employees suffer in silence.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="card stat-card" style="display: flex; flex-direction: column; align-items: center; text-align: center; padding: 36px 24px;">
            <span class="badge" style="background: rgba(197, 160, 89, 0.1); color: var(--accent);">Impact of Support</span>
            <div class="stat-number" style="font-size: clamp(3rem, 6vw, 4.5rem); font-weight: 900; color: var(--accent); line-height: 1.1; margin: 16px 0;">230<span style="font-size: 1.8rem; font-weight: 800;">%</span></div>
            <h4 style="font-size: 1.15rem; font-weight: 800; margin-bottom: 12px; color: var(--text-deep);">Return on Investment (ROI) of Psychological Care</h4>
            <p style="font-size: 0.92rem; color: var(--muted); line-height: 1.6; margin: 0;">
              International studies (such as Gallup) demonstrate that organizations investing in psychological safety and mental health support receive 2.3 times the economic return (230% ROI) through decreased turnover and higher productivity.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section>
      <div class="wrap">
        <div class="section-head">
          <p class="kicker">Why</p>
          <h2>Smaller organizations often suffer from a lack of external resources.</h2>
          <p class="muted">
            Even when business owners and managers care deeply about their employees, some personal struggles are difficult to share internally. Providing an external helpdesk helps employees clarify their thoughts early on, making it easier to connect them to professional medical support before issues become severe.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="grid three">
          <div class="card">
            <h3>Early Strain Detection</h3>
            <p>We provide an external outlet for worries before they escalate into long-term leave or resignation.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="card">
            <h3>Hard to Voice Internally</h3>
            <p>We receive employee worries from a neutral, external standpoint when they are hard to voice to bosses, peers, or HR.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="card">
            <h3>Support for Managers</h3>
            <p>We help managers organize thoughts regarding subordinate strain, harassment consultations, and anxieties before or after return-to-work.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section>
      <div class="wrap">
        <div class="section-head">
          <p class="kicker">Plans</p>
          <h2>Corporate Mental Health Helpdesk Plans</h2>
          <p class="muted">All displayed prices are tax inclusive. Extra consulting sessions are available at ¥10,000 per session.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="grid three">
          <div class="card">
            <span class="badge">Lite</span>
            <h3>¥15,000 / month</h3>
            <ul class="clean">
              <li>Helpdesk maintenance</li>
              <li>1 employee consultation / month</li>
              <li>Anonymized monthly report</li>
              <li>Additional session: ¥10,000 / each</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
          <div class="card soft-gradient">
            <span class="badge">Recommended</span>
            <h3>Standard: ¥30,000 / month</h3>
            <ul class="clean">
              <li>Helpdesk maintenance</li>
              <li>3 employee consultations / month</li>
              <li>Anonymized monthly report</li>
              <li>1 HR/Manager consultation / month</li>
              <li>Additional session: ¥10,000 / each</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
          <div class="card">
            <span class="badge">Custom Design</span>
            <h3>Premium: Custom Quote</h3>
            <ul class="clean">
              <li>Extra consultations</li>
              <li>Detailed reports</li>
              <li>Manager training sessions</li>
              <li>Workplace improvement suggestions</li>
              <li>Helpdesk internal announcement page setup support</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>
        <p class="notice-box" style="margin-top:18px;">
          Monthly corporate contracts generally have a minimum duration of 3 months. If you wish to cancel, please notify us by the end of the month prior to your desired cancellation month.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section>
      <div class="wrap grid two">
        <div>
          <p class="kicker">Report</p>
          <h2>Visualize workplace trends with monthly reports.</h2>
          <p>
            Personally identifiable information is never shared without explicit consent. We report total volume, category distribution, trends, and workplace environment suggestions in an entirely anonymized format.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <h3>Included in Monthly Reports</h3>
          <ul class="clean">
            <li>Total consultations & sessions conducted</li>
            <li>Stress categories & trends</li>
            <li>High-risk signs & workplace environment issues</li>
            <li>Improvement suggestions & check items for the next month</li>
            <li>Level of urgency</li>
          </ul>
          <h3 style="margin-top:18px;">Excluded from Reports</h3>
          <ul class="clean">
            <li>Names</li>
            <li>Personally identifiable information</li>
            <li>Specific consulting details without explicit consent</li>
            <li>Hard medical diagnoses or HR decisions</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section>
      <div class="wrap grid two">
        <div class="card">
          <h2>Confidentiality</h2>
          <p>
            We do not share personally identifiable employee consulting details with the client organization without explicit consent. We report cases, categories, and suggestions in an anonymized format.
            <strong>*If the low number of consultations might lead to the identification of individuals, we take precautions such as abstracting or omitting certain details.</strong>
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <h2>Emergency Exceptions</h2>
          <p>
            In cases where there is a risk of self-harm or harm to others, safety of life or body is concerned, or when deemed necessary for legal or safety duties, we prioritize safety and may coordinate with corporate coordinators, medical facilities, or public authorities within the necessary minimum scope.
            <strong>*Even in such cases, shared content is strictly limited to what is essential for safety, and we explain the details to the employee beforehand or afterwards whenever possible.</strong>
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section>
      <div class="wrap">
        <div class="section-head">
          <p class="kicker">Flow</p>
          <h2>Implementation Flow</h2>
        </div>
        <div class="grid five-cols flow">
          <div class="card"><h3>Inquiry</h3><p>Contact us via LINE or our contact form.</p></div>
          <div class="card"><h3>Hearing</h3><p>We discuss employee volume, current challenges, and desired support scope.</p></div>
          <div class="card"><h3>Agreement</h3><p>We finalize plans, contract terms, and reporting scope.</p></div>
          <div class="card"><h3>Introduction</h3><p>We guide you in introducing and announcing the helpdesk internally to employees.</p></div>
          <div class="card"><h3>Operation</h3><p>We launch employee consultations and begin monthly report delivery.</p></div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <ConsultationFlow lang="en" />
  </main>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .wrap { max-width: 1120px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 0 20px; }
  .hero { padding: 76px 0 48px; background: linear-gradient(180deg, #fffaf2 0%, var(--bg) 100%); }
  .kicker { color: var(--accent2); font-weight: 700; letter-spacing: .08em; text-transform: uppercase; font-size: 0.85rem; margin-bottom: 8px; }
  
  h1 { font-size: clamp(2rem, 5vw, 4.2rem); letter-spacing: .02em; line-height: 1.2; margin-bottom: 24px; font-weight: 800; }
  h2 { font-size: clamp(1.55rem, 3vw, 2.55rem); font-weight: 800; line-height: 1.3; margin-bottom: 16px; }
  h3 { font-size: 1.25rem; font-weight: 800; margin-bottom: 12px; }

  .lead { font-size: 1.12rem; color: #4d463e; max-width: 820px; }

  .btns { display: flex; gap: 12px; flex-wrap: wrap; margin-top: 28px; }
  .btn {
    display: inline-flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center;
    padding: 12px 24px; border-radius: 999px;
    text-decoration: none; font-weight: 800;
    border: 1px solid var(--line); background: var(--paper);
    transition: 0.3s;
  }
  .btn.primary { background: var(--accent2); color: white; border-color: var(--accent2); }
  .btn.secondary { background: #fff; color: var(--accent2); border: 1px solid var(--accent2); }

  .grid { display: grid; gap: 24px; }
  .grid.three { grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr); }
  .grid.two { grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr); }
  .grid.five-cols { grid-template-columns: repeat(5, 1fr); }

  .card {
    background: rgba(255, 253, 248, 0.94);
    border: 1px solid var(--line);
    border-radius: 24px;
    padding: 24px;
    box-shadow: var(--shadow);
    transition: 0.3s;
  }
  .card.soft-gradient { background: linear-gradient(135deg, #fffdf8, #f4eadc); border-color: var(--accent); }
  .card.soft-cta { background: linear-gradient(135deg, #fffdf8, #f4eadc); text-align: center; padding: 48px; border-color: var(--accent); }

  .badge {
    display: inline-block; padding: 4px 12px; border-radius: 999px;
    background: var(--soft); color: var(--accent); font-size: 0.75rem; font-weight: 800;
    margin-bottom: 12px;
  }

  .clean { list-style: none; padding: 0; margin: 12px 0 0; }
  .clean li { margin-bottom: 8px; position: relative; padding-left: 1.2rem; }
  .clean li::before { content: "・"; position: absolute; left: 0; color: var(--accent); font-weight: 800; }

  .notice-box {
    border-left: 5px solid var(--accent2);
    background: #eef7f5;
    padding: 18px 20px;
    border-radius: 16px;
    font-size: 0.95rem;
  }

  .flow { counter-reset: step; }
  .flow .card { position: relative; }
  .flow .card::before {
    counter-increment: step; content: "0" counter(step);
    display: block; margin-bottom: 12px;
    color: var(--accent2); font-weight: 800; font-size: 1.2rem;
  }

  @media (max-width: 900px) {
    .grid.three, .grid.five-cols { grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr); }
  }
  @media (max-width: 600px) {
    .grid.two, .grid.three, .grid.five-cols { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
    .hero { text-align: center; }
    .btns { justify-content: center; }
  }
</style>
